column5: Well I finally managed to get out for the first time this year. Went to Bennett lake with my wife and dad , went looking for Walleye and Pike but did not have to much luck with them. I caught a small Pike I released and my wife caught a decent one that my dad kept. I did manage to catch 5 nice bass ( I know, out of season and they all went back ) and a nice Crappie. I know what bass season opens up where im going to try to head to! Besides  the 5 I caught I had 4 get off right at the boat. Ill see if I can figure out how to post multiple pics, if not Ill post them individually .  Be warned, my ugly mug is in these pics, God did not bless me with good looks. View at your own risk!
]one of my wife with her Pike. This is only her second one she has ever caught.
Good job, just an FYI though, I wouldn't be taking pics with OOS fish and posting them anywhere online.   I know you're excited but you don't want to get yourself in trouble.

Good job, just an FYI though, I wouldn't be taking pics with OOS fish and posting them anywhere online.   I know you're excited but you don't want to get yourself in trouble. I will remove the pics of the bass, they were the first two I caught and took a quick pic of each before release.
I will remove the pics of the bass, they were the first two I caught and took a quick pic of each before release.   Alls good dude.

We are a tough bunch here LW. Keeps everyone on their toes an up to snuff on the law. Some laws we just make up. Your first mistake was posting a pic in the first place. A newbie recently was chased off after his first post and he posted a photo. Never been back since I believe.
I figured a pic of my mug would scare even the bravest away!
I figured a pic of my mug would scare even the bravest away!  Bah, you should see some of the cat fish people post    Go back to that lake and find the crappie!  There's gotta be more then one
He was 12 inches but I do not know how much he weighed as I could not find my scales. I'm thinking he was right around the 1 pound mark.
nice catch! havent caught any crappie myself this year
Where there's one crappie, there's bound to be more!!
